LNG Short-Term Freight More Than Doubled Last Month, Drewry Says

-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 
2011-06-09T07:25:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/lng-short-term-freight-more-than-doubled-last-month-drewry-says.html
Rates to ship short-term supplies of
liquefied natural gas more than doubled in May from a year
earlier, a shipping consultant said.  Freight rates for spot LNG vessels rose to $94,000 a day in
May from $35,000 a year earlier, Pranay Shukla, a Gurgaon,
India-based analyst at Drewry Maritime Services Ltd., said in a
monthly note e-mailed June 7. Long-term charter rates climbed 11
percent to $78,000 a day last month.  The LNG tanker fleet grew to 350 vessels last month from
343 a year earlier, with another 37 vessels on order, according
to the note. Freight rates for spot, or short-term, charters
averaged $83,000 a day this year from $40,700 in 2010, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
